Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.75,0:01:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,...salute you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.88,0:03:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Be gentle, Hanno.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.67,0:05:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We invoke you\Nby your great names
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.50,0:05:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to come to our aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.32,0:05:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Defeat the Romans.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.11,0:05:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Destroy their ships,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.76,0:05:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,their engines of war,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.46,0:05:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and their soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.42,0:05:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We will prevail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.38,0:05:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozalsces.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.78,0:05:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Arishat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.71,0:06:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanno.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.41,0:06:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You did not make\Nan offering today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.50,0:06:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I prefer to sacrifice a Roman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.69,0:06:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Where you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.17,0:06:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I am, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.17,0:06:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And where you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.92,0:06:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I am, too, forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.92,0:06:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.09,0:07:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The wind is too strong.\NFurl sail and strike water.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.83,0:07:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Furl sail,\Nstrike water!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.26,0:07:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Furl sail\Nand strike water!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.54,0:07:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Strike water!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.96,0:08:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They have no lands\Nbut the ones they've stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.00,0:08:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever they go,\Nthey leave destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.79,0:08:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and call it peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.36,0:08:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the last free city\Nin Africa Nova.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.27,0:08:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we go into battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.71,0:08:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray that your god\Nis with you.\NIf he is not, he is no god.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.42,0:08:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We've nothing to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.68,0:08:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Where death is, we are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.47,0:08:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Where we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.60,0:08:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,death is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.47,0:08:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay together and listen\Nfor my commands.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.78,0:08:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Your eyes up\Nand your head out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.78,0:09:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.78,0:09:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,[man] Ready your weapons!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.22,0:09:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.45,0:09:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We're ablaze on the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.58,0:09:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep formation!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.06,0:09:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.12,0:10:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Archers ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.81,0:10:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Release!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.52,0:10:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Nock!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.74,0:10:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.13,0:10:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Loose!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.44,0:10:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Archers!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.71,0:10:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.86,0:10:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- Raise the tower!\N- Raise the tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.87,0:11:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Back astern!\N- Back astern!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.36,0:11:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep cranking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.24,0:11:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop drawbridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.07,0:11:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The drawbridge is stuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.26,0:11:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.17,0:11:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Loose!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.10,0:11:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.42,0:12:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Archers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.99,0:13:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.21,0:13:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill her!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.34,0:13:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Arishat!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.72,0:14:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Arishat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.04,0:14:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Arishat!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.35,0:14:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll wait for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.31,0:15:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Check all the bodies!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.22,0:15:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.94,0:17:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I claim this city...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.43,0:17:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for the glory of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.21,0:17:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Vae victis.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.83,0:17:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Woe to the conquered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.54,0:17:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Next!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.37,0:17:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.17,0:18:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- Down the stairs!\N- Downstairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.53,0:19:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.66,0:19:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What damage have they\Ndone you, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.63,0:19:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Lift it up. Easy, easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.72,0:19:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.90,0:19:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Arishat?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.60,0:19:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I am sorry, my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.52,0:19:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I have not long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.52,0:19:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This galley
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.66,0:19:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is sailing us to something\NI cannot endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.14,0:19:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I am ready... to be taken\Nto another place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.36,0:19:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay here a while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.80,0:20:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember well\Nwhen you first\Nwere brought to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.54,0:20:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A lonely boy\Nfrom the desert.\NGuileless.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.72,0:20:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.07,0:20:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You embraced everything\Nwe taught you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.47,0:20:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You found Arishat's love.\NYour soul was replenished.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.86,0:20:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When I die,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.21,0:20:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,my ancestors will meet me\Nin the next world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.13,0:20:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Who will meet you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.52,0:20:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanno,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.83,0:20:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I am done.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.83,0:20:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not let them change\Nwhat you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.78,0:21:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen this boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.27,0:21:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Eama! Eama!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.88,0:21:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You must\Ngo alone now, Hanno.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.98,0:21:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Never let them find you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.55,0:21:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Go. Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.53,0:23:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.88,0:23:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Geta.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.41,0:23:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Caracalla.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.67,0:23:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,General Acacius.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.41,0:23:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I have taken Numidia\Nin your names
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.50,0:23:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that your dominion\Nmay eclipse that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.42,0:23:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of every emperor\Nthat came before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.68,0:23:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Crown him with laurels, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.08,0:24:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.83,0:24:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In honor\Nof your conquest,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.70,0:24:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,there will be games\Nin the Colosseum.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.06,0:24:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I require no games\Nin my honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.75,0:24:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Serving the Senate\Nand the people of Rome
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.37,0:24:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is honor enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.19,0:24:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You are too modest,\NAcacius.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.07,0:24:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not suit a general\Nas accomplished as yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.42,0:24:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The glory is yours,\Nnot mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.34,0:24:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I only ask for\Nsome respite from war
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.51,0:24:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to spend time\Nwith my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.12,0:24:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Your wife, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.65,0:24:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the privileges\Nwe have granted her?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.87,0:24:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is she now\Nto ignore such an occasion?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.04,0:24:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There are victories\Nyet still to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.40,0:24:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Persia.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.27,0:24:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,India.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.58,0:24:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Both... must be conquered.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.97,0:25:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Rome has so many subjects.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.63,0:25:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She must feed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.76,0:25:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They can eat war.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.90,0:25:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Your triumphs\Nwill be celebrated
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.86,0:25:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as a tribute\Nto the greatness
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.03,0:25:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Roman people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.71,0:25:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.99,0:26:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Macrinus of Thysdrus,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.52,0:26:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,master of gladiators!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.19,0:26:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay close.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.47,0:26:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Aediles\Nand the town councilors,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.95,0:26:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,distinguished guests,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.61,0:26:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,citizens of Antium,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.22,0:27:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,behold the fate
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.97,0:27:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of the conquered enemies\Nof Rome:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.93,0:27:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The barbarian Numidians\Nand their chieftain,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.45,0:27:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Jugurtha!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.62,0:28:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.74,0:29:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll buy him.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.15,0:29:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Halt! Who goes there?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.94,0:29:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,General.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.67,0:30:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.51,0:30:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I thank the gods\Nthat brought you back home safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.99,0:30:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank the Army.\NThey protected me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.78,0:30:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.00,0:30:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me feed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.37,0:31:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.12,0:31:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,To the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.30,0:31:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The arena\Nis a sacred temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.74,0:31:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,For the bravest of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.48,0:31:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the road to glory\Nruns through the arena.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.44,0:31:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The arena turns slaves\Ninto gladiators
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.57,0:31:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and gladiators into free men.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.71,0:31:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You have worms.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.24,0:31:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I know this one.\NHe eats monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.78,0:31:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Go. Sit. Eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.71,0:32:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.19,0:33:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanno, get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.55,0:33:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What is\Nyour native language?\NI speak them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.25,0:33:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't answer because\Nyou can't or because you won't?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.60,0:33:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.91,0:33:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Violence...\Nis the universal language.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.78,0:33:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Viggo,\Nput him through his paces.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.57,0:33:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He can fight an ape.\NLet's see if he\Ncan fight a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.25,0:34:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.91,0:34:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.61,0:34:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.00,0:34:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hose him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.18,0:35:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring him to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.58,0:35:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.84,0:35:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A strong jaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.37,0:35:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Good arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.37,0:35:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Better smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.73,0:35:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You will do well.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.03,0:35:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It is an art,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.99,0:35:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,choosing gladiators.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.30,0:35:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Some choose entertainers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.65,0:35:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Some choose brute force.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.78,0:35:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I choose rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.74,0:35:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Crowd loves blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.40,0:35:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And they love those who\Nlove blood as much as they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.23,0:35:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And you, my friend, rage
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.40,0:35:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,pours out of you like...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.06,0:35:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,like milk...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.24,0:35:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,from a whore's tit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.59,0:35:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be\Nquite the fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.41,0:36:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.07,0:36:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right,\Nyou do not fight for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.24,0:36:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I put you in the ring,\Nyou fight or you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.68,0:36:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The choice is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.94,0:36:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But whose head\Ncould I give you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.99,0:36:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that would satisfy this fury?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.69,0:36:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire Roman Army's.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.08,0:36:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.30,0:36:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.00,0:36:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The general will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.18,0:36:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,General?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.53,0:36:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- General Acacius?\N- Mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.84,0:36:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Use your rage\Nin my service,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.49,0:36:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will have his head\Nready for your sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.54,0:36:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Serve me and I will serve you.\NDeny me...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.93,0:36:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.51,0:36:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There are times I wished\Nyou'd abandoned me
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.33,0:36:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than\Nfight their wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.21,0:36:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I've made my choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.21,0:36:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I can live with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.26,0:37:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But my patience with those two\Nis at an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.96,0:37:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Leta?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.27,0:37:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You may go\Nto your quarters now.\NWe need nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.93,0:37:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,To hear wives and mothers\Nmourning their dead
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.63,0:37:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,on that beach at Numidia...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.85,0:37:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.64,0:37:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No more.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.51,0:37:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not waste
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.73,0:37:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,another generation\Nof young men for their vanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.48,0:37:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If I fight another campaign,\Nit must be to depose them.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.92,0:37:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,When will your troops\Narrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.83,0:37:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They land at Ostia\Nin ten days.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.27,0:38:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of them will be\Nloyal to you alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.88,0:38:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.37,0:38:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The emperors do not have\Nthe support of the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.06,0:38:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The people are weary\Nof the madness, the tyranny.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.85,0:38:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the dream of Rome\Nif her people are not free?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.36,0:38:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy yourself,\Neveryone,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.88,0:38:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to excess!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.97,0:38:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.86,0:39:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.90,0:39:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.08,0:39:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Excuse me. Macrinus!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.26,0:39:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew the provinces\Nwere not enough for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.00,0:39:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just here\N- for the games.\N- Ah, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.26,0:39:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't be disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.96,0:39:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Rome has all the games\Nthat men like you like to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.27,0:39:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Men like me, Thraex?\NMen like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.62,0:39:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I know nothing happens\Nin Rome unless you've\Ntasted it first.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.68,0:39:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What is my purpose here?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.34,0:39:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll find out soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.39,0:39:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this we hear\Nabout you being interested
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.65,0:39:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in standing for election\Nto the Senate, Macrinus?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.44,0:40:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Me? No, I'm, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.05,0:40:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know how\Nto use an abacus.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.61,0:40:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do understand that
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.62,0:40:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it's customary\Nfor your guests
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.01,0:40:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to make wagers\Nat these affairs?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.71,0:40:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How large a sum\Ndid you have in mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.54,0:40:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A thousand gold denarii?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.11,0:40:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.37,0:40:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Two?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.55,0:40:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Denarii.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.74,0:40:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand back! Stand back!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.13,0:40:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,My emperors.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.70,0:40:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Lords, ladies and gentlemen,\Nand senators.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.84,0:40:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,For your entertainment,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.84,0:40:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the art of combat!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.28,0:41:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,May I present
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.11,0:41:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the barbarian versus,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.28,0:41:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from my own stable,\Nthe mighty Vichek!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.64,0:41:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- This is your gladiator?\N- It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.69,0:41:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Three rounds,\Nhand to hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.35,0:41:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Swords!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.09,0:41:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We want swords.\NA fight to the death.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.70,0:41:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No quarter to be offered...\Nor given.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.75,0:41:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight now!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.28,0:41:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.58,0:41:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,let's not kill each other\Nfor their amusement.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.61,0:42:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Remarkable!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.70,0:42:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Remarkable!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.48,0:42:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thraex,\Nhe looked expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.79,0:43:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- Congratulations.\N- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.97,0:43:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.89,0:43:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,From where do you hail?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.15,0:43:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.12,0:43:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I said speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.42,0:43:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He is from the colonies,\NYour Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.21,0:43:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,His native tongue\Nis all he understands.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.04,0:43:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"The gates of hell\Nare open night and day.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.61,0:43:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Smooth is the descent,\Nand easy is the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.36,0:43:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.97,0:43:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to come back from hell
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.02,0:43:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and view the cheerful skies,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.93,0:43:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in this the task\Nand mighty labor lies."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.03,0:44:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Virgil, Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.47,0:44:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Poetry!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.86,0:44:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Very clever, Macrinus.\N- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.82,0:44:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I've grown so bored,\Nbut you surprise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.22,0:44:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To amuse you is my only wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.35,0:44:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We are amused,\Nwe are amused.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.18,0:44:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We are amused.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.92,0:44:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And we all look forward\Nto seeing your poet
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.10,0:44:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,perform in the arena.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.54,0:44:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,As do I, Your Majesties.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.24,0:44:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.89,0:44:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Viggo?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.20,0:44:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.74,0:45:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You fought well today,\Nbut you were lucky, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.57,0:45:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The lines you recited.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.18,0:45:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't learn that\Nin Africa, I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.62,0:45:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- A good verse travels far.\N- Mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.88,0:45:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Who taught you poetry?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.93,0:45:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A captured Roman officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.23,0:45:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I was posted guard over him\Nand he used to tell us tales
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.54,0:45:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to pass the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.37,0:45:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And what became\Nof this prisoner?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.68,0:45:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we ate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.50,0:45:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,As barbarians do.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.68,0:45:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As barbarians do.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.12,0:45:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And where were you born?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.21,0:45:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does my past matter\Nif it is my future
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.60,0:45:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to die for you in the arena?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.52,0:45:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me what use have I\Nfor Roman money.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.87,0:45:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A gladiator
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.36,0:45:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,can buy his own freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.14,0:45:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,His liberty.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.88,0:46:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The Roman dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.75,0:46:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the slave dreams\Nnot of freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.84,0:46:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but of a slave\Nto call his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.15,0:46:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Cicero.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.85,0:46:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what you were\Nraised on, Macrinus?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.94,0:46:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you have to do\Nfor Roman money?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.77,0:46:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You promised me a head.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.42,0:46:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Earn your keep\Nand you can have\Nanyone's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.45,0:46:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Father,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.37,0:46:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,protect us and guide us.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.69,0:47:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Senators.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.69,0:47:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.00,0:47:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My lady, I wish we were\Nmeeting in better times.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.31,0:47:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Better times will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.62,0:47:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And why are we here?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.10,0:47:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To take back the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.84,0:47:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And restore Rome\Nto where she should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.80,0:47:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,An exciting venture.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.98,0:47:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- When?\N- On the final day\Nof the games.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.37,0:47:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My army waits for my command\Nat Ostia.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.25,0:47:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Five thousand soldiers\Nloyal to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.47,0:47:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,will enter Rome\Nand then the Colosseum,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.95,0:47:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,where they will\Narrest the emperors
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.95,0:47:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for their crimes\Nagainst the Senate
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.43,0:47:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and their people.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.96,0:48:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, this plan\Nis ambitious and risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.05,0:48:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Rome will be yours\Nto administer and to--
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.88,0:48:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Marcus Aurelius talked\Nof restoring power\Nto the Senate,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.62,0:48:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but that was a generation ago.\NMuch has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.02,0:48:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The people\Nhave not seen hope
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.02,0:48:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,for many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.50,0:48:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But with time...\Nand guidance...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.81,0:48:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucilla, you are the daughter\Nof Marcus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.29,0:48:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He had my loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.08,0:48:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And so do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.34,0:48:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Senator Thraex?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.56,0:48:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Politics follows power,\Nmy lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.09,0:48:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Take back\Nwhat is rightfully yours...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.09,0:48:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Senate\Nwill support you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.23,0:48:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.55,0:49:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Food! Food!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.60,0:49:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was told of this place,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.08,0:49:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they never mentioned\Nthe stink.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.21,0:49:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be Hanno.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.78,0:49:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you'll have to\Nput up with me as I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.79,0:49:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's that up there?\NA wolf?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.62,0:49:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The twins there,\Nthey were outcasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.93,0:49:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Left in the hills to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.15,0:49:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That wolf found them\Nand she suckled them\Non her milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.07,0:49:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Raised by an animal.\NIt's in their blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.46,0:49:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.47,0:49:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know the chaos\Nthey brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.73,0:50:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This city infects\Neverything it touches.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.60,0:50:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I never dreamt\Nit would be so big.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.78,0:50:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't fall for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.61,0:50:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This city is diseased.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.91,0:50:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Food! Food!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.81,0:50:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You! Barbarian scum!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.17,0:50:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me.\NPlease, help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.94,0:51:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ah!\N- Thraex.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.04,0:51:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,About our wager.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.17,0:51:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. The barbarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.04,0:51:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I haven't forgotten,\NI always repay my debts.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.43,0:51:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was merely\Ngoing to suggest
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.39,0:51:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that perhaps your luck\Nmight change.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.44,0:51:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we say\Ndouble or quits?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.36,0:51:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ah.\N- Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.80,0:51:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.47,0:52:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Fresh meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.04,0:52:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Line up! Line up!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.55,0:52:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Play! Play!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.35,0:53:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Caracalla.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.36,0:53:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Geta.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.36,0:53:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Citizens of Rome!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.93,0:53:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,These sacred games
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.10,0:53:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are held to honor\Nthe victory of Rome
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.41,0:53:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,over the barbarians of Numidia.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.76,0:53:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Go! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.25,0:53:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And to honor\NRome's legionary commander,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.82,0:53:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,General Justus Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.12,0:53:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[man] Long live Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.87,0:53:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And with him
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.43,0:53:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucilla, the daughter\Nof Emperor Marcus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.92,0:53:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucilla![man] Mother of Rome!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.36,0:53:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.36,0:53:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,General.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.11,0:54:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.50,0:54:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.51,0:54:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.64,0:54:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.30,0:54:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not an orator
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.17,0:54:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,or a politician.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.00,0:54:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.14,0:54:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I have seen bravery\Nin men and women during war.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.10,0:54:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And even once in this arena.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.45,0:54:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you ask anything\Nof the gods...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.06,0:54:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,ask for that same bravery.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.72,0:54:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Rome needs it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.99,0:55:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.90,0:55:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.75,0:55:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,From the South Gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.36,0:55:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,fighters from the stable\Nof Macrinus of Thysdrus!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.94,0:55:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,From the stables
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.03,0:55:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of Emperors Caracalla\Nand Geta themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.68,0:55:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the undefeated champion:
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.34,0:55:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Glyceo the Destroyer!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.61,0:55:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.42,0:56:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.55,0:56:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hail Caesars!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.81,0:56:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Glyceo! Glyceo! Glyceo!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.92,0:56:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold together\Nand when it charges,\Nbreak for the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.18,0:56:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should I?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.27,0:56:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.32,0:56:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.54,0:56:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Break!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.50,0:56:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Cowards!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.86,0:57:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.96,0:57:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.28,0:59:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, it's that poet,\Nis it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.98,0:59:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.07,0:59:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That night was a blur.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.16,0:59:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"The gates of hell\Nare open night and day.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.90,0:59:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Smooth the desc--"\NI forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.08,0:59:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,"Smooth the descent..."
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.65,0:59:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,"Smooth is the descent,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.26,0:59:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,easy is the way."
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.66,0:59:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Shield!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.87,1:00:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Mercy! Mercy! Mercy!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.18,1:00:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.44,1:00:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucilla,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.27,1:00:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,shall we show mercy?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.66,1:00:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Mercy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.64,1:00:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No mercy!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.77,1:00:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life has been\Nspared by the gods--
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.73,1:00:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I would sooner face your blade\Nthan accept Roman mercy!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.84,1:01:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill! Kill! Kill!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.36,1:01:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill! Kill! Kill!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.98,1:01:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.10,1:02:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The road to freedom\Ndoesn't run\Nthrough the arena.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.54,1:02:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It leads to this.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.59,1:02:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to your cells.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.42,1:02:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.84,1:02:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.46,1:02:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"Gates of hell\Nare open night and day.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.72,1:02:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Smooth is the descent...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.47,1:03:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,...easy is the way."
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.47,1:03:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There, there, there, there.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.95,1:03:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And I've got you.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.39,1:03:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm Maximus,\Nthe savior of Rome!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.58,1:03:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Scatto and Argento.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.34,1:03:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucius is safe?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.53,1:04:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucius!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.29,1:04:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucius,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.29,1:04:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you're the sole heir\Nto the throne now.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.03,1:04:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There are men\Nwho want to kill you
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.42,1:04:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so they can take power.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.60,1:04:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise I'll bring you back\Nas soon as it's safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.91,1:04:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, why can't you\Ncome with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.61,1:04:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I have to\Nstay here for your sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.13,1:04:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the sake of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.22,1:04:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember who you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.79,1:04:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And that I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.40,1:04:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.66,1:04:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.97,1:04:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me your leg.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.19,1:04:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Go. Go!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.59,1:05:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.42,1:05:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.69,1:05:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Ravi. I'm a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.47,1:05:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Because... more men die\Nof infected wounds
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.09,1:05:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,than out there, in the arena.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.05,1:05:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This needs to be cleaned,\Nit needs to be stitched and
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.01,1:05:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it is going to hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.75,1:05:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.05,1:05:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Devil's Breath\Nand opium.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.71,1:05:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for the pain.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.19,1:05:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You should breathe in.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.89,1:05:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been here\Nso long now,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.50,1:05:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even notice anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.07,1:05:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I've done more amputations\Nthan I can count.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.99,1:05:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Where'd you\N- learn your trade?\N- Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.69,1:05:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a heavy hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.73,1:06:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to be\Na gladiator myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.30,1:06:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.78,1:06:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And would you have bested me?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.96,1:06:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In your prime, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.66,1:06:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In your current state,\NI could best you now.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.14,1:06:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily for you,\NI have put down my sword.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.45,1:06:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I spend my days
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.75,1:06:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,saving lives\Ninstead of taking them.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.84,1:06:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And why such a change\Nso late in life?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.19,1:06:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What we do in life
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.50,1:06:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,echoes in eternity.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.59,1:06:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like\NI know those words.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.34,1:06:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't take credit.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.99,1:06:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's written on\None of the tombs.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.64,1:06:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the bones of a gladiator.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.43,1:06:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[Macrinus] My champion!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.82,1:06:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I smell Devil's Breath!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.44,1:06:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My... champion.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.79,1:06:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear that crowd?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.53,1:07:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Did you hear that crowd?\N- Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.28,1:07:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You have something.\NI knew it from the start.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.97,1:07:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- Did you now?\N- Yes. The Greeks call it...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.59,1:07:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}thymos.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.24,1:07:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Smoke.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.29,1:07:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Rage.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.64,1:07:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That rage is your gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.38,1:07:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the great Achilles.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.29,1:07:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Never let it go.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.73,1:07:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It will carry you\Nto greatness,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.65,1:07:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,my champion.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.89,1:07:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.06,1:07:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for inviting me.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.11,1:07:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is truly an honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.20,1:08:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear you are\Nthe talk of the court.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.42,1:08:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.34,1:08:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We've met before.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.51,1:08:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- Have we?\N- Long ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.00,1:08:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.69,1:08:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the service\Nof your father's army
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.70,1:08:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,on his African campaign.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.96,1:08:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You served\Nwith my father?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.66,1:08:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.49,1:08:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the privilege
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.54,1:08:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of reading\Nhis "Meditations."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.23,1:08:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.45,1:08:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"The best revenge
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.54,1:08:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be unlike him\Nwho performed the injury."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.07,1:08:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear you've been\Narming half the legions
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.73,1:08:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in the entire empire,\Nand here, now, in Rome...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.08,1:08:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you're gaining influence\Nby sponsoring gladiators.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.13,1:08:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I do it for the love\Nof the sport.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.30,1:09:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And where did you find\Nthese gladiators?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.26,1:09:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They're usually\Nprisoners of war.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.96,1:09:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Or vagrants.\NWhy do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.53,1:09:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A man can choose to fight...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.15,1:09:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and stay alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.93,1:09:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same in life as it is\Nin the arena, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.50,1:09:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.24,1:09:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That is my father\Nas a youth.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.81,1:09:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She had a child?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.16,1:09:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.03,1:09:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's common knowledge.\NWhen Commodus was killed,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.51,1:09:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- the boy disappeared.\N- Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.43,1:09:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- But who would care?\N- Lucilla would care.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.56,1:09:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- More wine!\N- More wine!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.56,1:09:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He was of the royal bloodline,\Nafter all.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.79,1:09:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And his father?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.22,1:09:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ostensibly,\NLucius Verus.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.05,1:09:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,See, it was\Nan arranged marriage.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.88,1:09:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She was 14.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.10,1:10:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- Mm.\N- Females were not his taste.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.54,1:10:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- Nor mine, some days.\N- Nor yours!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.59,1:10:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.\NBy rumor, you see,\Nshe took lovers.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.89,1:10:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And by rumor,\Nthe real father...\Nwas Commodus.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.03,1:10:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Brotherly love,\N- you see?\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.55,1:10:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If he died,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.25,1:10:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- there has to be remains.\N- Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.78,1:10:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And if he lived,\Nthat would make him about...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.22,1:10:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, well,\Nlet's work it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.39,1:10:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He was about 12\N- when he died?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.87,1:10:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So that would make him...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.78,1:11:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My lady.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.26,1:11:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Gracchus.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.26,1:11:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- Please come.\N- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.94,1:11:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Gladiator...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.85,1:11:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,do you know me?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.25,1:11:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a family?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.08,1:11:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A wife. Arishat.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.87,1:11:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Arishat.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.44,1:11:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,She was killed\Nunder your husband's command.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.40,1:12:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Rome drowns\Nin its own blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.66,1:12:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet you enjoy\Nthe pleasures of the Colosseum.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.28,1:12:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There is much\Nyou do not understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.89,1:12:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucius.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.16,1:12:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not know\Nwho you think I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.55,1:12:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Hanno,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.55,1:12:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have no mother,\Nor none that I can remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.69,1:12:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.83,1:12:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If your son were here,\NI feel sure he would tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.00,1:12:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,not to grieve him.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.00,1:12:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,For he would not be the boy\Nthat you sent away.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.83,1:12:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy is dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.23,1:12:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You may think\NI have little worth.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.97,1:12:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You may think\NI betrayed you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.97,1:12:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But I need you to know...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.19,1:13:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,if you will not have\Nyour mother's love,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.24,1:13:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,then take\Nyour father's strength.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.29,1:13:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You need it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.99,1:13:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,His name was\NMaximus Decimus Meridius.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.56,1:13:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And I see him in you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.13,1:13:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.65,1:13:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,My lady, we must go at once!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.57,1:13:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucius, you were loved
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.09,1:13:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,by myself\Nand by your father.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.45,1:13:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name\Nwas on his lips--
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.97,1:13:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.82,1:14:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucius is alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.09,1:14:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you certain?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.96,1:14:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.22,1:14:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I know my son.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.62,1:14:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I spoke to him\Ntonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.89,1:14:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He may be lost to me\Nfor what I did,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.19,1:14:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but he lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.11,1:14:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The third day of the games\Nis tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.81,1:14:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Most fighters won't survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.46,1:14:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.20,1:14:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you must help him.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.55,1:14:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Help him?[crying] Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.95,1:14:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I failed him then.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.00,1:14:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.30,1:14:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot fail him now.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.09,1:14:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The army is in Ostia.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.61,1:14:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If we wait a few days...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.49,1:14:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He could be dead\Nby then.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.58,1:15:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.01,1:15:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I would willingly\Ngive my life for Rome,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.80,1:15:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but I will not\Ngive my son's.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.42,1:15:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And one.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.51,1:15:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And two.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.42,1:15:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And one.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.21,1:15:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Together.\NTiming, timing, timing!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.34,1:15:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And one. And two.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.04,1:15:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And one.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.13,1:15:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Pause, pause!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.88,1:15:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't get far\Nlike this.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.84,1:15:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Just him. You go.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.32,1:15:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.19,1:15:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how far you can go\Non your own without your team.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.32,1:15:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.93,1:15:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,One!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.07,1:15:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And two!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.11,1:15:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Timing, timing!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.90,1:15:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, more!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.56,1:16:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,More!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.01,1:16:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave him.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.12,1:16:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just vinegar,\Nmy friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.56,1:16:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be\Nno more opium for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.39,1:16:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There is plenty of pain waiting\Nfor you in the next life.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.17,1:16:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why\Nyou are so greedy for it\Nin this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.22,1:17:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you a free man, Ravi?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.75,1:17:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"Free."
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.27,1:17:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I am. Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.80,1:17:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I laid down my sword
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.45,1:17:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and I swore never\Nto pick it up again.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.54,1:17:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet\Nyou choose this hell?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.15,1:17:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.89,1:17:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What was your home before?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.46,1:17:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Varanasi.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.98,1:17:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And why don't you go back?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.33,1:17:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.90,1:17:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.16,1:17:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I met a woman.\NAh.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.08,1:17:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's always a woman.\N- Always.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.60,1:17:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She is from Londinium.\NBritannia. You know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.61,1:17:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So now...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.57,1:17:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,our sons,\Nthey speak only Latin.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.61,1:17:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter's eyes,\Nthey are as blue as yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.70,1:17:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We are Romans now.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.40,1:17:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I grew up hearing stories\Nat my grandfather's knee.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.23,1:18:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He used to talk\Nof the dream that was Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.89,1:18:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so fragile,\Nyou could only whisper it...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.11,1:18:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,or it would vanish.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.77,1:18:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.38,1:18:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,what was this dream?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.16,1:18:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A Rome where all could live\Nunder fair law and be protected.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.60,1:18:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A Rome of the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.13,1:18:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A Rome of hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.79,1:18:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Your grandfather,\Nhe sounds like\Na dangerous man.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.18,1:18:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.14,1:18:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The odds are against you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.67,1:18:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The odds\Nare always against me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.63,1:18:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, old man.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.93,1:18:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.24,1:18:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You should\N- get some rest. Hm?\N- Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.51,1:18:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Your men will need you\Nto lead them tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.27,1:19:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.09,1:19:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Survive!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.57,1:19:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In the name of Poseidon,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.45,1:19:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we celebrate the glory\Nof naval war.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.71,1:19:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They have archers.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.54,1:19:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Be ready.\NListen for my commands.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.06,1:19:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay together\Nand pull as one, yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.89,1:19:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.85,1:19:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes?\N- Yes!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.03,1:19:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we relive
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.86,1:19:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the Battle of Salamis!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.69,1:19:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Trojans\Nversus the Persians!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.79,1:20:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oars out![all] Oars!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.14,1:20:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And... pull!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.86,1:20:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Archers!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.99,1:20:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Archers!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.04,1:20:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.96,1:20:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.44,1:20:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.72,1:21:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull! To my time!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.85,1:21:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And... now!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.77,1:21:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Left side! Ready, and
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.25,1:21:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,ship oars now!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.29,1:21:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oars in! Oars in!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.86,1:21:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Get down!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.92,1:21:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And pull! And pull!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.67,1:21:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.11,1:21:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.94,1:21:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And right!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.99,1:21:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready to ram!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.64,1:21:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And brace! Brace!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.21,1:22:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone regroup!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.90,1:23:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Praetorians!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.25,1:23:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.82,1:23:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Move, move.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.70,1:23:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In the name of the emperors...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.96,1:23:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the victor is Hanno!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.24,1:23:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who did this?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.89,1:23:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who did this?!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.81,1:23:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- It was me!\N- I did it!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.12,1:24:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- I did it! I did it! I did it!\N- It was me!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.51,1:24:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Geta will want retribution\Nfor all of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.69,1:24:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you learn to shoot\Nin the same place
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.04,1:24:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you learned to recite poetry?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.61,1:24:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Be glad it wasn't me,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.87,1:24:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or that arrow\Nwould have found you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.02,1:24:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Be seated.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.98,1:24:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I have news for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.90,1:24:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He's here, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.51,1:24:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, still here.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.64,1:24:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Macrinus.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.17,1:24:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.87,1:24:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm listening.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.26,1:24:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You know\Nthis is my house now.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.96,1:25:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Your debt to me is\Nover 10,000 denarii.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.35,1:25:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.83,1:25:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I have other things. Uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.53,1:25:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Cattle. Art!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.40,1:25:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.10,1:25:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you... want?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.80,1:25:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth.\NThat's what I want.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.58,1:25:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing happens in Rome\Nwithout your knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.15,1:25:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You have\Nthe senators' trust.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.02,1:25:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You have\NLucilla's trust.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.33,1:25:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly,\Nyou have my trust.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.03,1:25:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You wish my... loyalty?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.08,1:25:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I own...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.17,1:25:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,your house.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.13,1:25:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I want your loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.53,1:25:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.14,1:25:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Tell me.\N- I have heard...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.01,1:25:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of a plot...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.58,1:25:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- to dethrone the emperors.\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.36,1:25:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But the plan\Nhas been delayed, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.93,1:26:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A gladiator is to be rescued\Nfrom the arena.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.15,1:26:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- Tonight.\N- Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.67,1:26:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't know why.\N- I know why. I know who.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.16,1:26:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Pack.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.86,1:26:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.32,1:26:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,[man] Open up!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.56,1:27:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Open for\Nthe emperors' guard!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.07,1:27:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lady, come with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.90,1:28:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to the civic virtue
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.25,1:28:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of men like Thraex\Nand Macrinus,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.12,1:28:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,your insurrection
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.56,1:28:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,has been revealed.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.39,1:28:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The honor,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.83,1:28:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the dignitas that Rome\Nhas bestowed upon you...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.18,1:28:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,all this you have forfeited\Nby your treachery.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.32,1:28:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Emperor Geta.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.97,1:28:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Torture me if you want,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.76,1:28:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but do not lecture me.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.24,1:28:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name\Nwill be forgotten!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.76,1:29:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Lost... to history.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.77,1:29:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You are damned,\NGeneral.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.90,1:29:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- You laugh.\N- You damn me?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.99,1:29:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.82,1:29:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is forgotten in time.\NEmpires fall. So do emperors.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.39,1:29:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why wait?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.22,1:29:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- I will gut him right now!\N- No, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.48,1:29:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let them be. Come! Come!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.88,1:29:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,His death must be public.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.79,1:29:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Public?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.40,1:29:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang his entrails\Nfrom the city gates!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.32,1:29:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And crucify her!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.62,1:29:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Crucify her!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.19,1:29:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Take them away!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.24,1:29:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,[Geta] Shh! Shh! Shh!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.73,1:29:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Macrinus.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.22,1:30:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.00,1:30:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In these last days,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.96,1:30:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I have come to think of you\Nnot as a subject
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.27,1:30:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but as a true friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.58,1:30:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.36,1:30:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NBut as a friend,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.10,1:30:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I must counsel caution.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.93,1:30:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius is a hero of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.76,1:30:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Crucifixion\Nis for thieves.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.33,1:30:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Christians.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.64,1:30:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's too common.\N- He is a traitor.\NHe must die.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.68,1:30:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.16,1:30:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the gods decide\Nhis fate in the Colosseum.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.26,1:30:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the gods decide.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.74,1:30:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, last night I woke,\Ndreaming of a dark river.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.32,1:30:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This time,\Nfor the first time,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.32,1:30:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I was crossing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.62,1:31:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.41,1:31:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know,\Nwhere I come from,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.98,1:31:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,crossing a river,\Nit represents forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.07,1:31:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Represents... salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.16,1:31:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Where I come from,\Nit means\Nyou're already dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.52,1:31:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But as I saw it,\NI was not afraid.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.74,1:31:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,For...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.52,1:31:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,For someone was waiting\Nfor me on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.00,1:31:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.02,1:31:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this man?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.89,1:31:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Scratched out?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.24,1:31:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Maximus.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.07,1:31:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw him fight once.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.12,1:31:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- He was magnificent.\N- Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.81,1:32:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. My time in the arena,\Nit was after his,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.86,1:32:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but many still talked of him\Nin whispers, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.17,1:32:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Spoke of him.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.17,1:32:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What he did.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.00,1:32:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I met him once.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.70,1:32:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He was kind.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.53,1:32:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He bowed to no one.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.88,1:32:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.62,1:32:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hmm?\N- Come. With me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.78,1:32:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When a rebel gladiator dies,\Nwe bury them here.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.04,1:32:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"What we do in life\Nechoes in eternity."
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.15,1:33:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Argento.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.11,1:33:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Scatto.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.02,1:34:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheers.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.33,1:34:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.42,1:34:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,For his treason\Nagainst the lives
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.59,1:34:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of the emperors\Nand the Roman state,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.73,1:34:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,General Justus Acacius,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.52,1:34:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,an enemy of the people!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.61,1:34:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.17,1:34:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,-  We love you, Acacius!\N- You are a hero!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.83,1:34:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.34,1:35:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Vae victis.{\i}[soldiers] General.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.06,1:35:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.24,1:35:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.42,1:35:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,From the vanquished city\Nof Numidia,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.65,1:35:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the victor of two conquests\Nin the Colosseum...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.96,1:35:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Go now. {\i1}Vae victis.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.83,1:35:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.75,1:36:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanno!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.19,1:36:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord, any honor I have,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.10,1:36:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- I will give it to you!\N- It's too late.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.89,1:36:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The Roman traitor or
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.24,1:36:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the barbarian hero.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.28,1:36:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the gods decide.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.16,1:36:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucius... wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.33,1:36:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.52,1:36:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a vessel.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.61,1:36:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Fill me with vengeance
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.83,1:36:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and vanquish the betrayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.89,1:36:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- We love you, Acacius!\N- Move it!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.29,1:37:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick it up!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.03,1:37:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Bravo, Hanno!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.51,1:37:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We love you, Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.04,1:37:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.12,1:37:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You will die!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.16,1:37:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know who you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.25,1:37:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucius Verus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.61,1:38:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius\Nhas raised his hand!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.61,1:38:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He has surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.49,1:38:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the gods decide.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.08,1:38:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The gods have rendered\Ntheir judgment.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.04,1:38:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Do what you must.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.65,1:38:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But on my death,\Nyou have to know...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.92,1:38:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I love your mother,\NLucilla.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.31,1:38:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And your father...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.44,1:38:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Maximus.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.79,1:38:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have died\Nfor him.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.01,1:38:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.97,1:39:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him live!\NPlease!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.80,1:39:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Live! Live! Live! Live!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.81,1:39:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.51,1:39:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,[Geta] Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.51,1:39:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Archers!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.86,1:39:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No![Geta] Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.82,1:39:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius! Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.43,1:39:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.22,1:39:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.74,1:39:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill him! Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.35,1:39:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.80,1:39:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.41,1:39:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.02,1:39:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.20,1:39:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.11,1:39:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Death will be\Ntoo good for you!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.56,1:40:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this how Rome\Ntreats its heroes?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.69,1:40:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.35,1:40:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If his life has no value,\Nwhat are yours worth?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.96,1:40:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The gods have spoken!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.98,1:40:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanno! Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.09,1:40:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,For our own safety,\Nwe should return to the palace.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.45,1:41:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.37,1:41:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay back! Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.99,1:42:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Arishat!
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.92,1:42:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a bargain.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.15,1:42:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave him to you.\NYou let him live.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.50,1:42:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And you got\Nwhat you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.28,1:42:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I always get what I want.\NWhy did you let him live?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.98,1:42:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You bought a gladiator,\Nnot a slave.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.55,1:42:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My will is my own.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.55,1:42:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.03,1:42:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How blue is your blood?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.82,1:43:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the heart of a Roman
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.47,1:43:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,beats in that chest.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:08.39,1:43:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest temple\NRome ever built.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.35,1:43:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The Colosseum.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.01,1:43:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this is\Nwhat they believe in.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.40,1:43:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Power.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.14,1:43:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They gather here to watch\Nthe strong strike down the weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.93,1:43:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There has to be\N- something else.\N- There is nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.89,1:43:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There has to be\N- another Rome.\N- There is no other Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.15,1:43:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- The "dream"?\N- Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.85,1:43:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The dream of Rome?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.85,1:43:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an old man's fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.16,1:43:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.64,1:43:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What was your name\Nbefore you traded it\Nfor a Roman one?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.69,1:43:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never know.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.95,1:43:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a destiny.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.05,1:43:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The gods delivered you to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.40,1:43:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be my instrument.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.23,1:44:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I will never be\Nyour instrument,\Nin this life or the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.80,1:44:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That will not be my destiny.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.03,1:44:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But I will see your end.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.70,1:44:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What else could I do?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.66,1:44:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He and his bitch\Nwere plotting to kill us.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.57,1:44:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you hear them?\NThey're calling for our heads!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.32,1:44:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Praetorians\Nwill put down this crowd.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.45,1:44:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- Like they have every other.\N- You brought this on us.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.28,1:44:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Filthy ape!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.37,1:44:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you should, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.20,1:45:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,take Dondus elsewhere\Nto comfort him?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.13,1:45:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive\Nmy brother's outburst.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.30,1:45:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The disease\Nthat infects his loins
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.91,1:45:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,has spread to his brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.96,1:45:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Every day he gets worse.\N- I will reason with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.33,1:45:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.55,1:45:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.99,1:45:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Caracalla, Caracalla!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.25,1:45:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, stand up.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.99,1:45:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Get up, get up.\NNot you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.17,1:45:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All right,\Nthere you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.65,1:45:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.08,1:45:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.74,1:46:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing's ever mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.48,1:46:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is ours, always.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.92,1:46:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in the womb...\Nhe tried...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.97,1:46:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to cut my umbilicus
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.40,1:46:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I couldn't have\Nany more air.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.32,1:46:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember that,\N- do you?\N- Certainly.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.67,1:46:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come, sit.\N- One cannot forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.11,1:46:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My conscience compels me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.41,1:46:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.94,1:46:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.24,1:46:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brother
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.50,1:46:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,means to blame you
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.03,1:46:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of\Nthe entire Senate...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.51,1:46:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But I did not do it!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.99,1:46:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,...for what's happening\Nin the streets.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.64,1:46:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- The chaos!\N- He's lying!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.12,1:46:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No testimony\Ncan be more damning
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.04,1:46:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,than one brother\Nagainst another.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.56,1:46:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lie!\NHe always lies!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.31,1:46:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He can be very persuasive.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.87,1:46:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So?\NWhat will they do to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:49.70,1:46:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I don't dare imagine.\NBut imagine this:
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.53,1:46:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What will they do to Dondus?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.71,1:47:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What will they do
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.63,1:47:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to Dondus?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.37,1:47:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.50,1:47:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.02,1:47:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Put down the blade.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:49.89,1:47:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.11,1:47:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- Give it to me.\N- You always lie!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.98,1:47:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it--
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.86,1:48:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me.\NLook at me. Look at me.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.21,1:48:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- Lie!\N- Listen to me.\NBreak the spell.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.69,1:48:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- Lie!\N- Break the spell!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.82,1:48:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always protected you.\NBecause I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.61,1:48:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back. Help me.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.28,1:48:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucius.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.44,1:48:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Never could have imagined\Nthe fates would lead us here.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.18,1:49:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet here we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.66,1:49:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything has\Nbrought us full circle.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.49,1:49:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You sent me away\Nand yet fate
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.67,1:49:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,brought me back\Nto the very ground\Nwhere he died.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.15,1:49:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This ring...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.02,1:49:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,belonged to my father.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.81,1:49:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave it\Nto your father,\NMaximus,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.95,1:49:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,as a token of trust.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.21,1:49:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave it to Acacius\Nfor his valor.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.70,1:49:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This ring belonged to my wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.88,1:49:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I shall wear it next to yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.63,1:50:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I am truly sorry for Acacius.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.42,1:50:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I could not see the man.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.42,1:50:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a soldier of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.25,1:50:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a plan.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.91,1:50:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He was readying troops\Nat Ostia
Dialogue: 0,1:50:15.39,1:50:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,under the command\Nof Darius Sextus.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.52,1:50:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Troops he was to lead\Nagainst the emperors.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.61,1:50:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Acacius. Maximus.\NMarcus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.10,1:50:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They lived and died\Nfor Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:32.19,1:50:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We all do.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.71,1:50:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true\Nthey intend to kill you?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:41.06,1:50:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,One man or another\Nhas had a sword\Nagainst my neck
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.15,1:50:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,since the day\Nmy father died.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.72,1:50:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But now\Nthat I've found you,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.51,1:50:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.69,1:50:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not afraid.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.56,1:50:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I've become well versed\Nin losing the things\Nthat I love.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:02.48,1:51:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But now that I've found you,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.83,1:51:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no desire\Nto lose you again.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.66,1:51:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- You stand like him.\N- Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:11.62,1:51:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Alert.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:13.88,1:51:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Proud.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:17.23,1:51:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not have his strength.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.71,1:51:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish that were true.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:24.24,1:51:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I were telling you\Nto flee this place.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.16,1:51:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Go now.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:45.56,1:51:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Strength and honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.26,1:51:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Strength and honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.58,1:52:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As Emperor,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:05.76,1:52:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I have convened
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.37,1:52:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the Senate to appoint\Nmy First Consul
Dialogue: 0,1:52:11.72,1:52:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and bestow upon him the power\Nto administer the military
Dialogue: 0,1:52:15.11,1:52:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and civic functions\Nof the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.21,1:52:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I name...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.69,1:52:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Citizen Dondus!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.13,1:52:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hail Dondus!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.23,1:52:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hail Dondus!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:42.75,1:52:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hail Dondus.\N- Hail Dondus!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:45.49,1:52:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hail Dondus!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:52.24,1:52:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As Second Consul...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.03,1:52:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I name...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.90,1:53:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Citizen...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.47,1:53:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Macrinus!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:07.30,1:53:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hail Macrinus!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.08,1:53:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hail Macrinus!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.65,1:53:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hail Macrinus!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.43,1:53:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be\Na triumphal parade\Nto celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:17.09,1:53:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be games
Dialogue: 0,1:53:19.40,1:53:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and mass executions.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.53,1:53:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the Empire!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.80,1:53:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the Empire!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:30.67,1:53:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the Empire!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.68,1:53:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.29,1:53:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I happen to have...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.56,1:53:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,with good fortune\Nand not a little skill...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:54.95,1:53:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the remaining emperor's ear.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:05.31,1:54:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I can speak logic to it...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:12.36,1:54:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and tame the madness\Nin the street. But...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:17.80,1:54:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to restore order...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:21.50,1:54:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I must have power...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:27.07,1:54:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and command
Dialogue: 0,1:54:29.81,1:54:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,over the Praetorian Army.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:37.65,1:54:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ballot...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.57,1:54:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or hand?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:45.09,1:54:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye![all] Aye!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:50.92,1:54:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your humble servant.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:56.67,1:54:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your hands down.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:00.89,1:55:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You can sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.95,1:55:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Rome must fall.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:20.30,1:55:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I need only\Ngive it a push.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:25.39,1:55:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And after Rome falls...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.53,1:55:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,...what then?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.05,1:55:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You are\Nyour father's child.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:37.10,1:55:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,His dream of Rome\Nwas never a dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.67,1:55:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a fiction.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.76,1:55:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,"The best revenge is
Dialogue: 0,1:55:45.19,1:55:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to become unlike the one\Nwho did the injury."
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.15,1:55:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I have made myself\Nunlike your father.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:54.20,1:55:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He spoke of dreams,\NI speak of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:57.86,1:56:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only truth\Nin my Rome
Dialogue: 0,1:56:01.86,1:56:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is the law\Nof the strongest.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:06.17,1:56:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was owned
Dialogue: 0,1:56:09.00,1:56:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,by an emperor.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:13.53,1:56:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I control an empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:16.70,1:56:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Where else but in Rome\Ncan a man do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:25.28,1:56:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you recognize\Nyour father's mark on me?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:34.59,1:56:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is anything
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.59,1:56:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you need...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:39.73,1:56:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in these last hours,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.38,1:56:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we will provide.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:49.78,1:56:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Your death will clear my path\Nto the throne.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:54.39,1:56:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow\Nthere will be games.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:57.48,1:56:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And at them...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:59.96,1:57:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I will prevail.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:15.33,1:57:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ravi!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:23.42,1:57:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you get me a message\Nto Ostia by morning?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:25.77,1:57:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What is in Ostia?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:27.60,1:57:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There is an army.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:31.30,1:57:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm asking you\Nto risk yourself, my friend,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:33.08,1:57:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in the service\Nof something greater.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:38.09,1:57:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ride to Ostia.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:40.79,1:57:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this ring\Nto General Darius Sextus.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:42.96,1:57:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:45.01,1:57:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Darius Sextus.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:47.79,1:57:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He will know it\Nas Acacius's ring.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.76,1:57:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:55.80,1:57:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,who shall I say has
Dialogue: 0,1:57:57.85,1:57:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,sent me with this ring?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:02.90,1:58:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Lucius Verus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:06.47,1:58:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The Prince of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:09.21,1:58:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell him\NI am summoning the army
Dialogue: 0,1:58:10.82,1:58:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to the defense\Nof a new Republic.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:21.74,1:58:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- Should I trust you?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:23.05,1:58:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I?Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:32.01,1:58:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ravi! I need your keys.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:40.80,1:58:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:20.37,1:59:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop! Come back!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:53.57,1:59:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Who gave you this?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:55.71,1:59:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucius Verus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:59.06,2:00:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Prince of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:53.46,2:00:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Must we kill Lucilla?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:58.16,2:01:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Until she dies,\Nyou will never know peace.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:03.77,2:01:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:15.74,2:01:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The people love her.\NHer death will incite the mob.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:18.44,2:01:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If she dies and the streets\Nrise up in anger,
Dialogue: 0,2:01:21.09,2:01:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I shall deliver them\NCaracalla's head
Dialogue: 0,2:01:22.66,2:01:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the people\Nshall acclaim me.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:24.18,2:01:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That, my friend,\Nis politics.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:30.58,2:01:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- Shall we?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:47.69,2:01:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Today will be\Nyour last fight, champion.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:50.91,2:01:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And our master\Nhas bestowed on you...
Dialogue: 0,2:01:54.91,2:01:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the wooden sword of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:01.31,2:02:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have to\Nearn it first.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:03.44,2:02:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, you're gonna\Ndefend your mother.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:28.68,2:02:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Wood or steel,\Na point is still a point!
Dialogue: 0,2:02:58.80,2:03:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait for me.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:19.13,2:03:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In honor
Dialogue: 0,2:03:21.00,2:03:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of the acclamation\Nof Emperor Caracalla,
Dialogue: 0,2:03:25.44,2:03:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,First Consul Dondus\Nand Second Consul Macrinus,
Dialogue: 0,2:03:31.49,2:03:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and as punishment\Nfor her conspiracy\Nagainst the empire,
Dialogue: 0,2:03:36.14,2:03:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,for her calumnies against\Nthe emperor's imperial bloodline
Dialogue: 0,2:03:40.67,2:03:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and for fomenting\Nmilitary mutiny
Dialogue: 0,2:03:43.02,2:03:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,along with her husband,
Dialogue: 0,2:03:44.59,2:03:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the queen will face\Ndivine justice
Dialogue: 0,2:03:48.37,2:03:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,at the hands\Nof the Praetorian Guard.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:16.92,2:04:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not a general.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:20.14,2:04:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But we are all soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:25.63,2:04:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And up until now,
Dialogue: 0,2:04:27.54,2:04:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we have fought for nothing more\Nthan another day's survival.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:31.89,2:04:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you\Nhave us do?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:35.07,2:04:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can return\Nto your cells
Dialogue: 0,2:04:36.42,2:04:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do not wish\Nto fight this battle.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:38.51,2:04:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Or...
Dialogue: 0,2:04:42.56,2:04:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you can join me.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:45.21,2:04:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And fight for a freedom\Nfar beyond these walls.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:47.69,2:04:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye!
Dialogue: 0,2:04:49.39,2:04:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There once was a time when\Nhonor meant something in Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:55.22,2:04:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In this Rome
Dialogue: 0,2:04:57.66,2:04:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I no longer believe\Nthat exists.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:59.92,2:05:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We must find it!
Dialogue: 0,2:05:04.19,2:05:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And know this:
Dialogue: 0,2:05:07.19,2:05:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Where death is, we are not.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:12.94,2:05:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Where we are,
Dialogue: 0,2:05:15.59,2:05:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,death is not!
Dialogue: 0,2:05:20.33,2:05:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,By my sword.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:23.51,2:05:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Strength and honor.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:25.38,2:05:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Strength and honor!
Dialogue: 0,2:05:27.38,2:05:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Strength and honor!
Dialogue: 0,2:05:29.17,2:05:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Strength and honor!
Dialogue: 0,2:05:55.72,2:05:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Let it not be said
Dialogue: 0,2:05:57.94,2:06:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that the emperor\Nis not merciful.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:01.16,2:06:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The queen will be granted\Na single gladiator
Dialogue: 0,2:06:06.77,2:06:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to defend her against\Nthe Praetorian Guard.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:20.48,2:06:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The champion, Hanno!
Dialogue: 0,2:06:28.36,2:06:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!
Dialogue: 0,2:07:37.47,2:07:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,2:07:43.43,2:07:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Summon the cavalry.\NPut this down at once.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:46.78,2:07:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is war! Real war!
Dialogue: 0,2:07:54.18,2:07:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The army of Acacius\Nis advancing\Njust outside of Rome, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:00.19,2:08:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We can still\Noutflank them.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:01.76,2:08:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They have only\N5,000 troops, no more.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:05.41,2:08:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How many are we?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:07.02,2:08:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Six thousand.\NPerhaps more.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:08.50,2:08:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Ride to the gate\Nand hold them.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:01.90,2:09:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Filthy scum!
Dialogue: 0,2:09:16.83,2:09:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucius!
Dialogue: 0,2:09:20.14,2:09:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me the bow.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:44.99,2:09:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Go, my son. Lucius--
Dialogue: 0,2:09:47.60,2:09:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh-sh-sh-sh...
Dialogue: 0,2:09:48.82,2:09:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Horse!
Dialogue: 0,2:11:23.00,2:11:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Will nothing\Nkill this barbarian?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:25.22,2:11:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is\NLucius Verus Aurelius!
Dialogue: 0,2:11:27.88,2:11:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A man does not become\Nemperor by bloodline alone.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:30.31,2:11:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be taken by force\Nand kept by force.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:33.14,2:11:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you such a man\Nas this?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:35.10,2:11:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't fight for power.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:36.62,2:11:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I fight to free Rome\Nfrom men like you
Dialogue: 0,2:11:39.45,2:11:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and to return it to them.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:41.06,2:11:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The gods themselves\Nwant Rome reborn.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:43.98,2:11:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They sent me...\Nto fulfill that task.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:47.02,2:11:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And what if your gods\Nsent me here to kill you?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:50.64,2:11:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:52.86,2:11:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time to end this, Macrinus!
Dialogue: 0,2:12:31.11,2:12:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hah!
Dialogue: 0,2:13:03.23,2:13:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Strength and honor,
Dialogue: 0,2:13:05.32,2:13:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,my son.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:40.20,2:14:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You look to me to speak.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:44.16,2:14:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I know not what\Nto say other than
Dialogue: 0,2:14:45.94,2:14:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we have all known\Ntoo much death.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:49.21,2:14:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Let no more blood be spilt\Nin the name of tyranny.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:56.65,2:14:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandfather,\NMarcus Aurelius,
Dialogue: 0,2:14:59.30,2:15:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,talked of a dream\Nthat would be Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:03.13,2:15:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A dream that my father,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:06.27,2:15:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Maximus Decimus Meridius,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:09.18,2:15:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,died for.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:11.92,2:15:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,An ideal.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:16.32,2:15:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,A city for the many\Nand a refuge\Nfor those in need.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:20.76,2:15:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A home worth fighting for.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:24.37,2:15:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A home that Maximus\Nspent his life defending.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:30.73,2:15:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That dream is lost.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:38.52,2:15:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But dare we...
Dialogue: 0,2:15:41.69,2:15:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,rebuild that dream\Ntogether?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:56.23,2:15:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What say you?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:04.37,2:16:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye!
Dialogue: 0,2:16:07.37,2:16:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye!
Dialogue: 0,2:16:09.42,2:16:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye!
Dialogue: 0,2:16:10.77,2:16:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye! Aye! Aye! Aye!
Dialogue: 0,2:17:19.79,2:17:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:13.58,2:18:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak to me, Father.
